summary:
The Security Council,
 Recalling previous resolutions and statements on Liberia, 
Welcoming the Secretary-General's report of 10 September 2004 and its recommendations,
 Recognizing ECOWAS' critical role in the Liberian peace process and AU's support,
 Noting substantial progress in disarmament phase of ex-combatants' programme,
 Recalling resolutions 1521 (2003) and 1532 (2004) on measures against individuals undermining peace,
1. Extends UNMIL's mandate until 19 September 2005;
2. Calls on Liberian parties to commit to the peace process and ensure free, fair and transparent elections by October 2005;
3. Calls on the international community to fund rehabilitation and reintegration phase and fulfil pledges made at the International Reconstruction Conference;
4. Requests the Secretary-General to report periodically on UNMIL's progress;
5. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
